177 class InfixCalculator { ----
178 typedef std::pair< InfixCalculatorTok, int64_t > ICToken; ----
179 SmallVector InfixOperatorStack; ----
180 SmallVector PostfixStack; ----
181 ----
182 bool isUnaryOperator(InfixCalculatorTok Op) const { 0
183 return Op == IC_NEG || Op == IC_NOT; 0
184 } ----
185 ----
186 public: ----
187 int64_t popOperand() { 0
188 assert (!PostfixStack.empty() && "Poped an empty stack!"); 0
189 ICToken Op = PostfixStack.pop_back_val(); 0
190 if (!(Op.first == IC_IMM || Op.first == IC_REGISTER)) 0
191 return -1; // The invalid Scale value will be caught later by checkScale 0
192 return Op.second; 0
193 } ----
194 void pushOperand(InfixCalculatorTok Op, int64_t Val = 0) { 0
195 assert ((Op == IC_IMM || Op == IC_REGISTER) && 0
196 "Unexpected operand!"); ----
197 PostfixStack.push_back(std::make_pair(Op, Val)); 0
198 } 0
199 ----
200 void popOperator() { InfixOperatorStack.pop_back(); } 0
201 void pushOperator(InfixCalculatorTok Op) { 0
202 // Push the new operator if the stack is empty. ----
203 if (InfixOperatorStack.empty()) { 0
204 InfixOperatorStack.push_back(Op); 0
205 return; 0
206 } ----
207 ----
208 // Push the new operator if it has a higher precedence than the operator ----
209 // on the top of the stack or the operator on the top of the stack is a ----
210 // left parentheses. ----
211 unsigned Idx = InfixOperatorStack.size() - 1; 0
212 InfixCalculatorTok StackOp = InfixOperatorStack[Idx]; 0
213 if (OpPrecedence[Op] > OpPrecedence[StackOp] || StackOp == IC_LPAREN) { 0
214 InfixOperatorStack.push_back(Op); 0
215 return; 0
216 } ----
217 ----
218 // The operator on the top of the stack has higher precedence than the ----
219 // new operator. ----
220 unsigned ParenCount = 0; 0
221 while (true) { ----
222 // Nothing to process. ----
223 if (InfixOperatorStack.empty()) 0
224 break; 0
225 ----
226 Idx = InfixOperatorStack.size() - 1; 0
227 StackOp = InfixOperatorStack[Idx]; 0
228 if (!(OpPrecedence[StackOp] >= OpPrecedence[Op] || ParenCount)) 0
229 break; 0
230 ----
231 // If we have an even parentheses count and we see a left parentheses, ----
232 // then stop processing. ----
233 if (!ParenCount && StackOp == IC_LPAREN) 0
234 break; 0
235 ----
236 if (StackOp == IC_RPAREN) { 0
237 ++ParenCount; 0
238 InfixOperatorStack.pop_back(); 0
239 } else if (StackOp == IC_LPAREN) { 0
240 --ParenCount; 0
241 InfixOperatorStack.pop_back(); 0
242 } else { ----
243 InfixOperatorStack.pop_back(); 0
244 PostfixStack.push_back(std::make_pair(StackOp, 0)); 0
245 } ----
246 } ----
247 // Push the new operator. ----
248 InfixOperatorStack.push_back(Op); 0
249 } ----
250 ----
251 int64_t execute() { 0
252 // Push any remaining operators onto the postfix stack. ----
253 while (!InfixOperatorStack.empty()) { 0
254 InfixCalculatorTok StackOp = InfixOperatorStack.pop_back_val(); 0
255 if (StackOp != IC_LPAREN && StackOp != IC_RPAREN) 0
256 PostfixStack.push_back(std::make_pair(StackOp, 0)); 0
257 } ----
258 ----
259 if (PostfixStack.empty()) 0
260 return 0; 0
261 ----
262 SmallVector OperandStack; 0
263 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PostfixStack.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
264 ICToken Op = PostfixStack[i]; 0
265 if (Op.first == IC_IMM || Op.first == IC_REGISTER) { 0
266 OperandStack.push_back(Op); 0
267 } else if (isUnaryOperator(Op.first)) { 0
268 assert (OperandStack.size() > 0 && "Too few operands."); 0
269 ICToken Operand = OperandStack.pop_back_val(); 0
270 assert (Operand.first == IC_IMM && 0
271 "Unary operation with a register!"); ----
272 switch (Op.first) { 0
273 default: 0
274 report_fatal_error("Unexpected operator!"); 0
275 break; ----
276 case IC_NEG: 0
277 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, -Operand.second)); 0
278 break; 0
279 case IC_NOT: 0
280 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, ~Operand.second)); 0
281 break; 0
282 } ----
283 } else { ----
284 assert (OperandStack.size() > 1 && "Too few operands."); 0
285 int64_t Val; ----
286 ICToken Op2 = OperandStack.pop_back_val(); 0
287 ICToken Op1 = OperandStack.pop_back_val(); 0
288 switch (Op.first) { 0
289 default: 0
290 report_fatal_error("Unexpected operator!"); 0
291 break; ----
292 case IC_PLUS: 0
293 Val = Op1.second + Op2.second; 0
294 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
295 break; 0
296 case IC_MINUS: 0
297 Val = Op1.second - Op2.second; 0
298 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
299 break; 0
300 case IC_MULTIPLY: 0
301 assert (Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
302 "Multiply operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
303 Val = Op1.second * Op2.second; 0
304 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
305 break; 0
306 case IC_DIVIDE: 0
307 assert (Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
308 "Divide operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
309 assert (Op2.second != 0 && "Division by zero!"); 0
310 Val = Op1.second / Op2.second; 0
311 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
312 break; 0
313 case IC_MOD: 0
314 assert (Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
315 "Modulo operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
316 Val = Op1.second % Op2.second; 0
317 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
318 break; 0
319 case IC_OR: 0
320 assert (Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
321 "Or operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
322 Val = Op1.second | Op2.second; 0
323 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
324 break; 0
325 case IC_XOR: 0
326 assert(Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
327 "Xor operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
328 Val = Op1.second ^ Op2.second; 0
329 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
330 break; 0
331 case IC_AND: 0
332 assert (Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
333 "And operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
334 Val = Op1.second & Op2.second; 0
335 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
336 break; 0
337 case IC_LSHIFT: 0
338 assert (Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
339 "Left shift operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
340 Val = Op1.second << Op2.second; 0
341 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
342 break; 0
343 case IC_RSHIFT: 0
344 assert (Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
345 "Right shift operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
346 Val = Op1.second >> Op2.second; 0
347 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
348 break; 0
349 case IC_EQ: 0
350 assert(Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
351 "Equals operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
352 Val = (Op1.second == Op2.second) ? -1 : 0; 0
353 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
354 break; 0
355 case IC_NE: 0
356 assert(Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
357 "Not-equals operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
358 Val = (Op1.second != Op2.second) ? -1 : 0; 0
359 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
360 break; 0
361 case IC_LT: 0
362 assert(Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
363 "Less-than operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
364 Val = (Op1.second < Op2.second) ? -1 : 0; 0
365 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
366 break; 0
367 case IC_LE: 0
368 assert(Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
369 "Less-than-or-equal operation with an immediate and a " ----
370 "register!"); ----
371 Val = (Op1.second <= Op2.second) ? -1 : 0; 0
372 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
373 break; 0
374 case IC_GT: 0
375 assert(Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
376 "Greater-than operation with an immediate and a register!"); ----
377 Val = (Op1.second > Op2.second) ? -1 : 0; 0
378 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
379 break; 0
380 case IC_GE: 0
381 assert(Op1.first == IC_IMM && Op2.first == IC_IMM && 0
382 "Greater-than-or-equal operation with an immediate and a " ----
383 "register!"); ----
384 Val = (Op1.second >= Op2.second) ? -1 : 0; 0
385 OperandStack.push_back(std::make_pair(IC_IMM, Val)); 0
386 break; 0
387 } ----
388 } ----
389 } ----
390 assert (OperandStack.size() == 1 && "Expected a single result."); 0
391 return OperandStack.pop_back_val().second; 0
392 } 0

672 case IES_OFFSET: ----
673 State = IES_PLUS; 0
674 IC.pushOperator(IC_PLUS); 0
675 if (CurrState == IES_REGISTER && PrevState != IES_MULTIPLY) { 0
676 // If we already have a BaseReg, then assume this is the IndexReg with ----
677 // no explicit scale. ----
678 if (!BaseReg) { 0
679 BaseReg = TmpReg; 0
680 } else { ----
681 if (IndexReg) 0
682 return regsUseUpError(ErrMsg); 0
683 IndexReg = TmpReg; 0
684 Scale = 0; 0
685 } ----
686 } ----
687 break; 0
688 } ----
689 PrevState = CurrState; 0
690 return false; 0
691 } ----
692 bool onMinus(StringRef &ErrMsg) { 0
693 IntelExprState CurrState = State; 0
694 switch (State) { 0
695 default: 0
696 State = IES_ERROR; 0
697 break; 0
698 case IES_OR: 0
699 case IES_XOR: ----
700 case IES_AND: ----
701 case IES_EQ: ----
702 case IES_NE: ----
703 case IES_LT: ----
704 case IES_LE: ----
705 case IES_GT: ----
706 case IES_GE: ----
707 case IES_LSHIFT: ----
708 case IES_RSHIFT: ----
709 case IES_PLUS: ----
710 case IES_NOT: ----
711 case IES_MULTIPLY: ----
712 case IES_DIVIDE: ----
713 case IES_MOD: ----
714 case IES_LPAREN: ----
715 case IES_RPAREN: ----
716 case IES_LBRAC: ----
717 case IES_RBRAC: ----
718 case IES_INTEGER: ----
719 case IES_REGISTER: ----
720 case IES_INIT: ----
721 case IES_OFFSET: ----
722 State = IES_MINUS; 0
723 // push minus operator if it is not a negate operator ----
724 if (CurrState == IES_REGISTER || CurrState == IES_RPAREN || 0
725 CurrState == IES_INTEGER || CurrState == IES_RBRAC || 0
726 CurrState == IES_OFFSET) ----
727 IC.pushOperator(IC_MINUS); 0
728 else if (PrevState == IES_REGISTER && CurrState == IES_MULTIPLY) { 0
729 // We have negate operator for Scale: it's illegal ----
730 ErrMsg = "Scale can't be negative"; 0
731 return true; 0
732 } else ----
733 IC.pushOperator(IC_NEG); 0
734 if (CurrState == IES_REGISTER && PrevState != IES_MULTIPLY) { 0
735 // If we already have a BaseReg, then assume this is the IndexReg with ----
736 // no explicit scale. ----
737 if (!BaseReg) { 0
738 BaseReg = TmpReg; 0
739 } else { ----
740 if (IndexReg) 0
741 return regsUseUpError(ErrMsg); 0
742 IndexReg = TmpReg; 0
743 Scale = 0; 0
744 } ----
745 } ----
746 break; 0
747 } ----
748 PrevState = CurrState; 0
749 return false; 0
750 } ----
751 void onNot() { 0
752 IntelExprState CurrState = State; 0
753 switch (State) { 0
754 default: 0
755 State = IES_ERROR; 0
756 break; 0
757 case IES_OR: 0
758 case IES_XOR: ----
759 case IES_AND: ----
760 case IES_EQ: ----
761 case IES_NE: ----
762 case IES_LT: ----
763 case IES_LE: ----
764 case IES_GT: ----
765 case IES_GE: ----
766 case IES_LSHIFT: ----
767 case IES_RSHIFT: ----
768 case IES_PLUS: ----
769 case IES_MINUS: ----
770 case IES_NOT: ----
771 case IES_MULTIPLY: ----
772 case IES_DIVIDE: ----
773 case IES_MOD: ----
774 case IES_LPAREN: ----
775 case IES_LBRAC: ----
776 case IES_INIT: ----
777 State = IES_NOT; 0
778 IC.pushOperator(IC_NOT); 0
779 break; 0
780 } ----
781 PrevState = CurrState; 0
782 } 0
783 bool onRegister(unsigned Reg, StringRef &ErrMsg) { 0
784 IntelExprState CurrState = State; 0
785 switch (State) { 0
786 default: 0
787 State = IES_ERROR; 0
788 break; 0
789 case IES_PLUS: 0
790 case IES_LPAREN: ----
791 case IES_LBRAC: ----
792 State = IES_REGISTER; 0
793 TmpReg = Reg; 0
794 IC.pushOperand(IC_REGISTER); 0
795 break; 0
796 case IES_MULTIPLY: 0
797 // Index Register - Scale * Register ----
798 if (PrevState == IES_INTEGER) { 0
799 if (IndexReg) 0
800 return regsUseUpError(ErrMsg); 0
801 State = IES_REGISTER; 0
802 IndexReg = Reg; 0
803 // Get the scale and replace the 'Scale * Register' with '0'. ----
804 Scale = IC.popOperand(); 0
805 if (checkScale(Scale, ErrMsg)) 0
806 return true; 0
807 IC.pushOperand(IC_IMM); 0
808 IC.popOperator(); 0
809 } else { ----
810 State = IES_ERROR; 0
811 } ----
812 break; 0
813 } ----
814 PrevState = CurrState; 0
815 return false; 0
816 } ----
817 bool onIdentifierExpr(const MCExpr *SymRef, StringRef SymRefName, 0
818 const InlineAsmIdentifierInfo &IDInfo, ----
819 const AsmTypeInfo &Type, bool ParsingMSInlineAsm, ----
820 StringRef &ErrMsg) { ----
821 // InlineAsm: Treat an enum value as an integer ----
822 if (ParsingMSInlineAsm) 0
823 if (IDInfo.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_EnumVal)) 0
824 return onInteger(IDInfo.Enum.EnumVal, ErrMsg); 0
825 // Treat a symbolic constant like an integer ----
826 if (auto *CE = dyn_cast(SymRef)) 0
827 return onInteger(CE->getValue(), ErrMsg); 0
828 PrevState = State; 0
829 switch (State) { 0
830 default: 0
831 State = IES_ERROR; 0
832 break; 0
833 case IES_CAST: 0
834 case IES_PLUS: ----
835 case IES_MINUS: ----
836 case IES_NOT: ----
837 case IES_INIT: ----
838 case IES_LBRAC: ----
839 case IES_LPAREN: ----
840 if (setSymRef(SymRef, SymRefName, ErrMsg)) 0
841 return true; 0
842 MemExpr = true; 0
843 State = IES_INTEGER; 0
844 IC.pushOperand(IC_IMM); 0
845 if (ParsingMSInlineAsm) 0
846 Info = IDInfo; 0
847 setTypeInfo(Type); 0
848 break; 0
849 } ----
850 return false; 0
851 } ----
852 bool onInteger(int64_t TmpInt, StringRef &ErrMsg) { 0
853 IntelExprState CurrState = State; 0
854 switch (State) { 0
855 default: 0
856 State = IES_ERROR; 0
857 break; 0
858 case IES_PLUS: 0
859 case IES_MINUS: ----
860 case IES_NOT: ----
861 case IES_OR: ----
862 case IES_XOR: ----
863 case IES_AND: ----
864 case IES_EQ: ----
865 case IES_NE: ----
866 case IES_LT: ----
867 case IES_LE: ----
868 case IES_GT: ----
869 case IES_GE: ----
870 case IES_LSHIFT: ----
871 case IES_RSHIFT: ----
872 case IES_DIVIDE: ----
873 case IES_MOD: ----
874 case IES_MULTIPLY: ----
875 case IES_LPAREN: ----
876 case IES_INIT: ----
877 case IES_LBRAC: ----
878 State = IES_INTEGER; 0
879 if (PrevState == IES_REGISTER && CurrState == IES_MULTIPLY) { 0
880 // Index Register - Register * Scale ----
881 if (IndexReg) 0
882 return regsUseUpError(ErrMsg); 0
883 IndexReg = TmpReg; 0
884 Scale = TmpInt; 0
885 if (checkScale(Scale, ErrMsg)) 0
886 return true; 0
887 // Get the scale and replace the 'Register * Scale' with '0'. ----
888 IC.popOperator(); 0
889 } else { ----
890 IC.pushOperand(IC_IMM, TmpInt); 0
891 } ----
892 break; 0
893 } ----
894 PrevState = CurrState; 0
895 return false; 0
896 } ----

898 PrevState = State; 0
899 switch (State) { 0
900 default: 0
901 State = IES_ERROR; 0
902 break; 0
903 case IES_INTEGER: 0
904 case IES_REGISTER: ----
905 case IES_RPAREN: ----
906 State = IES_MULTIPLY; 0
907 IC.pushOperator(IC_MULTIPLY); 0
908 break; 0
909 } ----
910 } 0

922 } ----
923 } 0

935 } ----
936 } 0
937 bool onLBrac() { 0
938 if (BracCount) 0
939 return true; 0
940 PrevState = State; 0
941 switch (State) { 0
942 default: 0
943 State = IES_ERROR; 0
944 break; 0
945 case IES_RBRAC: 0
946 case IES_INTEGER: ----
947 case IES_RPAREN: ----
948 State = IES_PLUS; 0
949 IC.pushOperator(IC_PLUS); 0
950 CurType.Length = 1; 0
951 CurType.Size = CurType.ElementSize; 0
952 break; 0
953 case IES_INIT: 0
954 case IES_CAST: ----
955 assert(!BracCount && "BracCount should be zero on parsing's start"); 0
956 State = IES_LBRAC; 0
957 break; 0
958 } ----
959 MemExpr = true; 0
960 BracketUsed = true; 0
961 BracCount++; 0
962 return false; 0
963 } ----
964 bool onRBrac(StringRef &ErrMsg) { 0

966 switch (State) { 0

969 break; 0
970 case IES_INTEGER: 0
971 case IES_OFFSET: ----
972 case IES_REGISTER: ----
973 case IES_RPAREN: ----
974 if (BracCount-- != 1) { 0
975 ErrMsg = "unexpected bracket encountered"; 0
976 return true; 0
977 } ----
978 State = IES_RBRAC; 0
979 if (CurrState == IES_REGISTER && PrevState != IES_MULTIPLY) { 0
980 // If we already have a BaseReg, then assume this is the IndexReg with ----
981 // no explicit scale. ----
982 if (!BaseReg) { 0
983 BaseReg = TmpReg; 0
984 } else { ----
985 if (IndexReg) 0
986 return regsUseUpError(ErrMsg); 0
987 IndexReg = TmpReg; 0
988 Scale = 0; 0
989 } ----
990 } ----
991 break; 0
992 } ----
993 PrevState = CurrState; 0
994 return false; 0
995 } ----

1044 bool onOffset(const MCExpr *Val, SMLoc OffsetLoc, StringRef ID, 0
1045 const InlineAsmIdentifierInfo &IDInfo, ----
1046 bool ParsingMSInlineAsm, StringRef &ErrMsg) { ----
1047 PrevState = State; 0
1048 switch (State) { 0
1049 default: 0
1050 ErrMsg = "unexpected offset operator expression"; 0
1051 return true; 0
1052 case IES_PLUS: 0
1053 case IES_INIT: ----
1054 case IES_LBRAC: ----
1055 if (setSymRef(Val, ID, ErrMsg)) 0
1056 return true; 0
1057 OffsetOperator = true; 0
1058 OffsetOperatorLoc = OffsetLoc; 0
1059 State = IES_OFFSET; 0
1060 // As we cannot yet resolve the actual value (offset), we retain ----
1061 // the requested semantics by pushing a '0' to the operands stack ----
1062 IC.pushOperand(IC_IMM); 0
1063 if (ParsingMSInlineAsm) { 0
1064 Info = IDInfo; 0
1065 } ----
1066 break; 0
1067 } ----
1068 return false; 0
1069 } ----

1073 default: 0
1074 State = IES_ERROR; 0
1075 break; 0
1076 case IES_LPAREN: 0
1077 setTypeInfo(Info); 0
1078 State = IES_CAST; 0
1079 break; 0
1080 } ----
1081 } 0

1088 if (MatchingInlineAsm) { 0
1089 if (!getLexer().isAtStartOfStatement()) 0
1090 Parser.eatToEndOfStatement(); 0
1091 return false; 0
1092 } ----
1093 return Parser.Error(L, Msg, Range); 0
1094 } ----

1227 void SwitchMode(unsigned mode) { 0
1228 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI(); 0
1229 FeatureBitset AllModes({X86::Is64Bit, X86::Is32Bit, X86::Is16Bit}); 0
1230 FeatureBitset OldMode = STI.getFeatureBits() & AllModes; 0
1231 FeatureBitset FB = ComputeAvailableFeatures( 0
1232 STI.ToggleFeature(OldMode.flip(mode))); 0
1233 setAvailableFeatures(FB); 0
1234 ----
1235 assert(FeatureBitset({mode}) == (STI.getFeatureBits() & AllModes)); 0
1236 } 0

1239 if (is16BitMode()) return 16; 0
1240 if (is32BitMode()) return 32; 0
1241 if (is64BitMode()) return 64; 0
1242 llvm_unreachable("invalid mode"); 0
1243 } ----

1293 static bool CheckBaseRegAndIndexRegAndScale(unsigned BaseReg, unsigned IndexReg, 0
1294 unsigned Scale, bool Is64BitMode, ----
1295 StringRef &ErrMsg) { ----
1296 // If we have both a base register and an index register make sure they are ----
1297 // both 64-bit or 32-bit registers. ----
1298 // To support VSIB, IndexReg can be 128-bit or 256-bit registers. ----
1299 ----
1300 if (BaseReg != 0 && 0
1301 !(BaseReg == X86::RIP || BaseReg == X86::EIP || 0
1302 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(BaseReg) || 0
1303 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR32RegClassID].contains(BaseReg) || 0
1304 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR64RegClassID].contains(BaseReg))) { 0
1305 ErrMsg = "invalid base+index expression"; 0
1306 return true; 0
1307 } ----
1308 ----
1309 if (IndexReg != 0 && 0
1310 !(IndexReg == X86::EIZ || IndexReg == X86::RIZ || 0
1311 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1312 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR32RegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1313 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR64RegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1314 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR128XRegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1315 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR256XRegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1316 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR512RegClassID].contains(IndexReg))) { 0
1317 ErrMsg = "invalid base+index expression"; 0
1318 return true; 0
1319 } ----
1320 ----
1321 if (((BaseReg == X86::RIP || BaseReg == X86::EIP) && IndexReg != 0) || 0
1322 IndexReg == X86::EIP || IndexReg == X86::RIP || 0
1323 IndexReg == X86::ESP || IndexReg == X86::RSP) { 0
1324 ErrMsg = "invalid base+index expression"; 0
1325 return true; 0
1326 } ----
1327 ----
1328 // Check for use of invalid 16-bit registers. Only BX/BP/SI/DI are allowed, ----
1329 // and then only in non-64-bit modes. ----
1330 if (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(BaseReg) && 0
1331 (Is64BitMode || (BaseReg != X86::BX && BaseReg != X86::BP && 0
1332 BaseReg != X86::SI && BaseReg != X86::DI))) { 0
1333 ErrMsg = "invalid 16-bit base register"; 0
1334 return true; 0
1335 } ----
1336 ----
1337 if (BaseReg == 0 && 0
1338 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(IndexReg)) { 0
1339 ErrMsg = "16-bit memory operand may not include only index register"; 0
1340 return true; 0
1341 } ----
1342 ----
1343 if (BaseReg != 0 && IndexReg != 0) { 0
1344 if (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR64RegClassID].contains(BaseReg) && 0
1345 (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1346 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR32RegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1347 IndexReg == X86::EIZ)) { ----
1348 ErrMsg = "base register is 64-bit, but index register is not"; 0
1349 return true; 0
1350 } ----
1351 if (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR32RegClassID].contains(BaseReg) && 0
1352 (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1353 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR64RegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1354 IndexReg == X86::RIZ)) { ----
1355 ErrMsg = "base register is 32-bit, but index register is not"; 0
1356 return true; 0
1357 } ----
1358 if (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(BaseReg)) { 0
1359 if (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR32RegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
1360 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR64RegClassID].contains(IndexReg)) { 0
1361 ErrMsg = "base register is 16-bit, but index register is not"; 0
1362 return true; 0
1363 } ----
1364 if ((BaseReg != X86::BX && BaseReg != X86::BP) || 0
1365 (IndexReg != X86::SI && IndexReg != X86::DI)) { 0
1366 ErrMsg = "invalid 16-bit base/index register combination"; 0
1367 return true; 0
1368 } ----
1369 } ----
1370 } ----
1371 ----
1372 // RIP/EIP-relative addressing is only supported in 64-bit mode. ----
1373 if (!Is64BitMode && BaseReg != 0 && 0
1374 (BaseReg == X86::RIP || BaseReg == X86::EIP)) { 0
1375 ErrMsg = "IP-relative addressing requires 64-bit mode"; 0
1376 return true; 0
1377 } ----
1378 ----
1379 return checkScale(Scale, ErrMsg); 0
1380 } ----
1381 ----
1382 bool X86AsmParser::MatchRegisterByName(MCRegister &RegNo, StringRef RegName, 0
1383 SMLoc StartLoc, SMLoc EndLoc) { ----
1384 // If we encounter a %, ignore it. This code handles registers with and ----
1385 // without the prefix, unprefixed registers can occur in cfi directives. ----
1386 RegName.consume_front("%"); 0
1387 ----
1388 RegNo = MatchRegisterName(RegName); 0
1389 ----
1390 // If the match failed, try the register name as lowercase. ----
1391 if (RegNo == 0) 0
1392 RegNo = MatchRegisterName(RegName.lower()); 0
1393 ----
1394 // The "flags" and "mxcsr" registers cannot be referenced directly. ----
1395 // Treat it as an identifier instead. ----
1396 if (isParsingMSInlineAsm() && isParsingIntelSyntax() && 0
1397 (RegNo == X86::EFLAGS || RegNo == X86::MXCSR)) 0
1398 RegNo = 0; 0
1399 ----
1400 if (!is64BitMode()) { 0
1401 // FIXME: This should be done using Requires and ----
1402 // Requires so "eiz" usage in 64-bit instructions can be also ----
1403 // checked. ----
1404 if (RegNo == X86::RIZ || RegNo == X86::RIP || 0
1405 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR64RegClassID].contains(RegNo) || 0
1406 X86II::isX86_64NonExtLowByteReg(RegNo) || 0
1407 X86II::isX86_64ExtendedReg(RegNo)) { 0
1408 return Error(StartLoc, 0
1409 "register %" + RegName + " is only available in 64-bit mode", 0
1410 SMRange(StartLoc, EndLoc)); 0
1411 } ----
1412 } ----
1413 ----
1414 // If this is "db[0-15]", match it as an alias ----
1415 // for dr[0-15]. ----
1416 if (RegNo == 0 && RegName.startswith("db")) { 0
1417 if (RegName.size() == 3) { 0
1418 switch (RegName[2]) { 0
1419 case '0': 0
1420 RegNo = X86::DR0; 0
1421 break; 0
1422 case '1': 0
1423 RegNo = X86::DR1; 0
1424 break; 0
1425 case '2': 0
1426 RegNo = X86::DR2; 0
1427 break; 0
1428 case '3': 0
1429 RegNo = X86::DR3; 0
1430 break; 0
1431 case '4': 0
1432 RegNo = X86::DR4; 0
1433 break; 0
1434 case '5': 0
1435 RegNo = X86::DR5; 0
1436 break; 0
1437 case '6': 0
1438 RegNo = X86::DR6; 0
1439 break; 0
1440 case '7': 0
1441 RegNo = X86::DR7; 0
1442 break; 0
1443 case '8': 0
1444 RegNo = X86::DR8; 0
1445 break; 0
1446 case '9': 0
1447 RegNo = X86::DR9; 0
1448 break; 0
1449 } ----
1450 } else if (RegName.size() == 4 && RegName[2] == '1') { 0
1451 switch (RegName[3]) { 0
1452 case '0': 0
1453 RegNo = X86::DR10; 0
1454 break; 0
1455 case '1': 0
1456 RegNo = X86::DR11; 0
1457 break; 0
1458 case '2': 0
1459 RegNo = X86::DR12; 0
1460 break; 0
1461 case '3': 0
1462 RegNo = X86::DR13; 0
1463 break; 0
1464 case '4': 0
1465 RegNo = X86::DR14; 0
1466 break; 0
1467 case '5': 0
1468 RegNo = X86::DR15; 0
1469 break; 0
1470 } ----
1471 } ----
1472 } ----
1473 ----
1474 if (RegNo == 0) { 0
1475 if (isParsingIntelSyntax()) 0
1476 return true; 0
1477 return Error(StartLoc, "invalid register name", SMRange(StartLoc, EndLoc)); 0
1478 } ----
1479 return false; 0
1480 } ----
1481 ----
1482 bool X86AsmParser::ParseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, 0
1483 SMLoc &EndLoc, bool RestoreOnFailure) { ----
1484 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
1485 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer(); 0
1486 RegNo = 0; 0
1487 ----
1488 SmallVector Tokens; 0
1489 auto OnFailure = [RestoreOnFailure, &Lexer, &Tokens]() { 0
1490 if (RestoreOnFailure) { 0
1491 while (!Tokens.empty()) { 0
1492 Lexer.UnLex(Tokens.pop_back_val()); 0
1493 } ----
1494 } ----
1495 }; 0
1496 ----
1497 const AsmToken &PercentTok = Parser.getTok(); 0
1498 StartLoc = PercentTok.getLoc(); 0
1499 ----
1500 // If we encounter a %, ignore it. This code handles registers with and ----
1501 // without the prefix, unprefixed registers can occur in cfi directives. ----
1502 if (!isParsingIntelSyntax() && PercentTok.is(AsmToken::Percent)) { 0
1503 Tokens.push_back(PercentTok); 0
1504 Parser.Lex(); // Eat percent token. 0
1505 } ----
1506 ----
1507 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
1508 EndLoc = Tok.getEndLoc(); 0
1509 ----
1510 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) { 0
1511 OnFailure(); 0
1512 if (isParsingIntelSyntax()) return true; 0
1513 return Error(StartLoc, "invalid register name", 0
1514 SMRange(StartLoc, EndLoc)); 0
1515 } ----
1516 ----
1517 if (MatchRegisterByName(RegNo, Tok.getString(), StartLoc, EndLoc)) { 0
1518 OnFailure(); 0
1519 return true; 0
1520 } ----
1521 ----
1522 // Parse "%st" as "%st(0)" and "%st(1)", which is multiple tokens. ----
1523 if (RegNo == X86::ST0) { 0
1524 Tokens.push_back(Tok); 0
1525 Parser.Lex(); // Eat 'st' 0
1526 ----
1527 // Check to see if we have '(4)' after %st. ----
1528 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::LParen)) 0
1529 return false; 0
1530 // Lex the paren. ----
1531 Tokens.push_back(Parser.getTok()); 0
1532 Parser.Lex(); 0
1533 ----
1534 const AsmToken &IntTok = Parser.getTok(); 0
1535 if (IntTok.isNot(AsmToken::Integer)) { 0
1536 OnFailure(); 0
1537 return Error(IntTok.getLoc(), "expected stack index"); 0
1538 } ----
1539 switch (IntTok.getIntVal()) { 0
1540 case 0: RegNo = X86::ST0; break; 0
1541 case 1: RegNo = X86::ST1; break; 0
1542 case 2: RegNo = X86::ST2; break; 0
1543 case 3: RegNo = X86::ST3; break; 0
1544 case 4: RegNo = X86::ST4; break; 0
1545 case 5: RegNo = X86::ST5; break; 0
1546 case 6: RegNo = X86::ST6; break; 0
1547 case 7: RegNo = X86::ST7; break; 0
1548 default: 0
1549 OnFailure(); 0
1550 return Error(IntTok.getLoc(), "invalid stack index"); 0
1551 } ----
1552 ----
1553 // Lex IntTok ----
1554 Tokens.push_back(IntTok); 0
1555 Parser.Lex(); 0
1556 if (Lexer.isNot(AsmToken::RParen)) { 0
1557 OnFailure(); 0
1558 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "expected ')'"); 0
1559 } ----
1560 ----
1561 EndLoc = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc(); 0
1562 Parser.Lex(); // Eat ')' 0
1563 return false; 0
1564 } ----
1565 ----
1566 EndLoc = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc(); 0
1567 ----
1568 if (RegNo == 0) { 0
1569 OnFailure(); 0
1570 if (isParsingIntelSyntax()) return true; 0
1571 return Error(StartLoc, "invalid register name", 0
1572 SMRange(StartLoc, EndLoc)); 0
1573 } ----
1574 ----
1575 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token. 0
1576 return false; 0
1577 } 0
1578 ----
1579 bool X86AsmParser::parseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, 0
1580 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
1581 return ParseRegister(RegNo, StartLoc, EndLoc, /*RestoreOnFailure=*/false); 0
1582 } ----
1583 ----
1584 OperandMatchResultTy X86AsmParser::tryParseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, 0
1585 SMLoc &StartLoc, ----
1586 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
1587 bool Result = ----
1588 ParseRegister(RegNo, StartLoc, EndLoc, /*RestoreOnFailure=*/true); 0
1589 bool PendingErrors = getParser().hasPendingError(); 0
1590 getParser().clearPendingErrors(); 0
1591 if (PendingErrors) 0
1592 return MatchOperand_ParseFail; 0
1593 if (Result) 0
1594 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
1595 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
1596 } ----

1599 bool Parse32 = is32BitMode() || Code16GCC; 0
1600 unsigned Basereg = is64BitMode() ? X86::RSI : (Parse32 ? X86::ESI : X86::SI); 0
1601 const MCExpr *Disp = MCConstantExpr::create(0, getContext()); 0
1602 return X86Operand::CreateMem(getPointerWidth(), /*SegReg=*/0, Disp, 0
1603 /*BaseReg=*/Basereg, /*IndexReg=*/0, /*Scale=*/1, ----
1604 Loc, Loc, 0); 0
1605 } ----

1611 return X86Operand::CreateMem(getPointerWidth(), /*SegReg=*/0, Disp, 0
1612 /*BaseReg=*/Basereg, /*IndexReg=*/0, /*Scale=*/1, ----
1613 Loc, Loc, 0); 0

1616 bool X86AsmParser::IsSIReg(unsigned Reg) { 0
1617 switch (Reg) { 0
1618 default: llvm_unreachable("Only (R|E)SI and (R|E)DI are expected!"); 0
1619 case X86::RSI: 0
1620 case X86::ESI: ----
1621 case X86::SI: ----
1622 return true; 0
1623 case X86::RDI: 0
1624 case X86::EDI: ----
1625 case X86::DI: ----
1626 return false; 0
1627 } ----
1628 } ----
1629 ----
1630 unsigned X86AsmParser::GetSIDIForRegClass(unsigned RegClassID, unsigned Reg, 0
1631 bool IsSIReg) { ----
1632 switch (RegClassID) { 0
1633 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected register class"); 0
1634 case X86::GR64RegClassID: 0
1635 return IsSIReg ? X86::RSI : X86::RDI; 0
1636 case X86::GR32RegClassID: 0
1637 return IsSIReg ? X86::ESI : X86::EDI; 0
1638 case X86::GR16RegClassID: 0
1639 return IsSIReg ? X86::SI : X86::DI; 0
1640 } ----
1641 } ----
1642 ----
1643 void X86AsmParser::AddDefaultSrcDestOperands( 0
1644 OperandVector& Operands, std::unique_ptr &&Src, ----
1645 std::unique_ptr &&Dst) { ----
1646 if (isParsingIntelSyntax()) { 0
1647 Operands.push_back(std::move(Dst)); 0
1648 Operands.push_back(std::move(Src)); 0
1649 } ----
1650 else { ----
1651 Operands.push_back(std::move(Src)); 0
1652 Operands.push_back(std::move(Dst)); 0
1653 } ----
1654 } 0
1655 ----
1656 bool X86AsmParser::VerifyAndAdjustOperands(OperandVector &OrigOperands, 0
1657 OperandVector &FinalOperands) { ----
1658 ----
1659 if (OrigOperands.size() > 1) { 0
1660 // Check if sizes match, OrigOperands also contains the instruction name ----
1661 assert(OrigOperands.size() == FinalOperands.size() + 1 && 0
1662 "Operand size mismatch"); ----
1663 ----
1664 SmallVector, 2> Warnings; 0
1665 // Verify types match ----
1666 int RegClassID = -1; 0
1667 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < FinalOperands.size(); ++i) { 0
1668 X86Operand &OrigOp = static_cast(*OrigOperands[i + 1]); 0
1669 X86Operand &FinalOp = static_cast(*FinalOperands[i]); 0
1670 ----
1671 if (FinalOp.isReg() && 0
1672 (!OrigOp.isReg() || FinalOp.getReg() != OrigOp.getReg())) 0
1673 // Return false and let a normal complaint about bogus operands happen ----
1674 return false; 0
1675 ----
1676 if (FinalOp.isMem()) { 0
1677 ----
1678 if (!OrigOp.isMem()) 0
1679 // Return false and let a normal complaint about bogus operands happen ----
1680 return false; 0
1681 ----
1682 unsigned OrigReg = OrigOp.Mem.BaseReg; 0
1683 unsigned FinalReg = FinalOp.Mem.BaseReg; 0
1684 ----
1685 // If we've already encounterd a register class, make sure all register ----
1686 // bases are of the same register class ----
1687 if (RegClassID != -1 && 0
1688 !X86MCRegisterClasses[RegClassID].contains(OrigReg)) { 0
1689 return Error(OrigOp.getStartLoc(), 0
1690 "mismatching source and destination index registers"); 0
1691 } ----
1692 ----
1693 if (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR64RegClassID].contains(OrigReg)) 0
1694 RegClassID = X86::GR64RegClassID; 0
1695 else if (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR32RegClassID].contains(OrigReg)) 0
1696 RegClassID = X86::GR32RegClassID; 0
1697 else if (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(OrigReg)) 0
1698 RegClassID = X86::GR16RegClassID; 0
1699 else ----
1700 // Unexpected register class type ----
1701 // Return false and let a normal complaint about bogus operands happen ----
1702 return false; 0
1703 ----
1704 bool IsSI = IsSIReg(FinalReg); 0
1705 FinalReg = GetSIDIForRegClass(RegClassID, FinalReg, IsSI); 0
1706 ----
1707 if (FinalReg != OrigReg) { 0
1708 std::string RegName = IsSI ? "ES:(R|E)SI" : "ES:(R|E)DI"; 0
1709 Warnings.push_back(std::make_pair( 0
1710 OrigOp.getStartLoc(), 0
1711 "memory operand is only for determining the size, " + RegName + 0
1712 " will be used for the location")); ----
1713 } 0
1714 ----
1715 FinalOp.Mem.Size = OrigOp.Mem.Size; 0
1716 FinalOp.Mem.SegReg = OrigOp.Mem.SegReg; 0
1717 FinalOp.Mem.BaseReg = FinalReg; 0
1718 } ----
1719 } ----
1720 ----
1721 // Produce warnings only if all the operands passed the adjustment - prevent ----
1722 // legal cases like "movsd (%rax), %xmm0" mistakenly produce warnings ----
1723 for (auto &WarningMsg : Warnings) { 0
1724 Warning(WarningMsg.first, WarningMsg.second); 0
1725 } ----
1726 ----
1727 // Remove old operands ----
1728 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < FinalOperands.size(); ++i) 0
1729 OrigOperands.pop_back(); 0
1730 } 0
1731 // OrigOperands.append(FinalOperands.begin(), FinalOperands.end()); ----
1732 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < FinalOperands.size(); ++i) 0
1733 OrigOperands.push_back(std::move(FinalOperands[i])); 0
1734 ----
1735 return false; 0
1736 } ----
1737 ----
1738 bool X86AsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Name) { 0
1739 if (isParsingIntelSyntax()) 0
1740 return parseIntelOperand(Operands, Name); 0
1741 ----
1742 return parseATTOperand(Operands); 0
1743 } ----
1744 ----
1745 bool X86AsmParser::CreateMemForMSInlineAsm( 0
1746 unsigned SegReg, const MCExpr *Disp, unsigned BaseReg, unsigned IndexReg, ----
1747 unsigned Scale, SMLoc Start, SMLoc End, unsigned Size, StringRef Identifier, ----
1748 const InlineAsmIdentifierInfo &Info, OperandVector &Operands) { ----
1749 // If we found a decl other than a VarDecl, then assume it is a FuncDecl or ----
1750 // some other label reference. ----
1751 if (Info.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_Label)) { 0
1752 // Create an absolute memory reference in order to match against ----
1753 // instructions taking a PC relative operand. ----
1754 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateMem(getPointerWidth(), Disp, Start, 0
1755 End, Size, Identifier, ----
1756 Info.Label.Decl)); 0
1757 return false; 0
1758 } ----
1759 // We either have a direct symbol reference, or an offset from a symbol. The ----
1760 // parser always puts the symbol on the LHS, so look there for size ----
1761 // calculation purposes. ----
1762 unsigned FrontendSize = 0; 0
1763 void *Decl = nullptr; 0
1764 bool IsGlobalLV = false; 0
1765 if (Info.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_Var)) { 0
1766 // Size is in terms of bits in this context. ----
1767 FrontendSize = Info.Var.Type * 8; 0
1768 Decl = Info.Var.Decl; 0
1769 IsGlobalLV = Info.Var.IsGlobalLV; 0
1770 } ----
1771 // It is widely common for MS InlineAsm to use a global variable and one/two ----
1772 // registers in a mmory expression, and though unaccessible via rip/eip. ----
1773 if (IsGlobalLV && (BaseReg || IndexReg)) { 0
1774 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateMem(getPointerWidth(), Disp, Start, 0
1775 End, Size, Identifier, Decl, 0, ----
1776 BaseReg && IndexReg)); 0
1777 return false; 0
1778 } ----
1779 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateMem( 0
1780 getPointerWidth(), SegReg, Disp, BaseReg, IndexReg, Scale, Start, End, ----
1781 Size, ----
1782 /*DefaultBaseReg=*/X86::RIP, Identifier, Decl, FrontendSize)); ----
1783 return false; 0
1784 } ----
1785 ----
1786 // Some binary bitwise operators have a named synonymous ----
1787 // Query a candidate string for being such a named operator ----
1788 // and if so - invoke the appropriate handler ----
1789 bool X86AsmParser::ParseIntelNamedOperator(StringRef Name, 0
1790 IntelExprStateMachine &SM, ----
1791 bool &ParseError, SMLoc &End) { ----
1792 // A named operator should be either lower or upper case, but not a mix... ----
1793 // except in MASM, which uses full case-insensitivity. ----
1794 if (Name.compare(Name.lower()) && Name.compare(Name.upper()) && 0
1795 !getParser().isParsingMasm()) 0
1796 return false; 0
1797 if (Name.equals_insensitive("not")) { 0
1798 SM.onNot(); 0
1799 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("or")) { 0
1800 SM.onOr(); 0
1801 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("shl")) { 0
1802 SM.onLShift(); 0
1803 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("shr")) { 0
1804 SM.onRShift(); 0
1805 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("xor")) { 0
1806 SM.onXor(); 0
1807 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("and")) { 0
1808 SM.onAnd(); 0
1809 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("mod")) { 0
1810 SM.onMod(); 0
1811 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("offset")) { 0
1812 SMLoc OffsetLoc = getTok().getLoc(); 0
1813 const MCExpr *Val = nullptr; 0
1814 StringRef ID; 0
1815 InlineAsmIdentifierInfo Info; 0
1816 ParseError = ParseIntelOffsetOperator(Val, ID, Info, End); 0
1817 if (ParseError) 0
1818 return true; 0
1819 StringRef ErrMsg; 0
1820 ParseError = 0
1821 SM.onOffset(Val, OffsetLoc, ID, Info, isParsingMSInlineAsm(), ErrMsg); 0
1822 if (ParseError) 0
1823 return Error(SMLoc::getFromPointer(Name.data()), ErrMsg); 0
1824 } else { ----
1825 return false; 0
1826 } ----
1827 if (!Name.equals_insensitive("offset")) 0
1828 End = consumeToken(); 0
1829 return true; 0
1830 } ----
1831 bool X86AsmParser::ParseMasmNamedOperator(StringRef Name, 0
1832 IntelExprStateMachine &SM, ----
1833 bool &ParseError, SMLoc &End) { ----
1834 if (Name.equals_insensitive("eq")) { 0
1835 SM.onEq(); 0
1836 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("ne")) { 0
1837 SM.onNE(); 0
1838 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("lt")) { 0
1839 SM.onLT(); 0
1840 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("le")) { 0
1841 SM.onLE(); 0
1842 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("gt")) { 0
1843 SM.onGT(); 0
1844 } else if (Name.equals_insensitive("ge")) { 0
1845 SM.onGE(); 0
1846 } else { ----
1847 return false; 0
1848 } ----
1849 End = consumeToken(); 0
1850 return true; 0
1851 } ----
1852 ----
1853 // Check if current intel expression append after an operand. ----
1854 // Like: [Operand][Intel Expression] ----
1855 void X86AsmParser::tryParseOperandIdx(AsmToken::TokenKind PrevTK, 0
1856 IntelExprStateMachine &SM) { ----
1857 if (PrevTK != AsmToken::RBrac) 0
1858 return; 0
1859 ----
1860 SM.setAppendAfterOperand(); 0
1861 } ----
1862 ----
1863 bool X86AsmParser::ParseIntelExpression(IntelExprStateMachine &SM, SMLoc &End) { 0
1864 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
1865 StringRef ErrMsg; 0
1866 ----
1867 AsmToken::TokenKind PrevTK = AsmToken::Error; 0
1868 ----
1869 if (getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->isPositionIndependent()) 0
1870 SM.setPIC(); 0
1871 ----
1872 bool Done = false; 0
1873 while (!Done) { 0
1874 // Get a fresh reference on each loop iteration in case the previous ----
1875 // iteration moved the token storage during UnLex(). ----
1876 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
1877 ----
1878 bool UpdateLocLex = true; 0
1879 AsmToken::TokenKind TK = getLexer().getKind(); 0
1880 ----
1881 switch (TK) { 0
1882 default: 0
1883 if ((Done = SM.isValidEndState())) 0
1884 break; 0
1885 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "unknown token in expression"); 0
1886 case AsmToken::Error: 0
1887 return Error(getLexer().getErrLoc(), getLexer().getErr()); 0
1888 break; ----
1889 case AsmToken::EndOfStatement: 0
1890 Done = true; 0
1891 break; 0
1892 case AsmToken::Real: 0
1893 // DotOperator: [ebx].0 ----
1894 UpdateLocLex = false; 0
1895 if (ParseIntelDotOperator(SM, End)) 0
1896 return true; 0
1897 break; 0
1898 case AsmToken::Dot: 0
1899 if (!Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
1900 if ((Done = SM.isValidEndState())) 0
1901 break; 0
1902 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "unknown token in expression"); 0
1903 } ----
1904 // MASM allows spaces around the dot operator (e.g., "var . x") ----
1905 Lex(); 0
1906 UpdateLocLex = false; 0
1907 if (ParseIntelDotOperator(SM, End)) 0
1908 return true; 0
1909 break; 0
1910 case AsmToken::Dollar: 0
1911 if (!Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
1912 if ((Done = SM.isValidEndState())) 0
1913 break; 0
1914 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "unknown token in expression"); 0
1915 } ----
1916 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1917 case AsmToken::String: { ----
1918 if (Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
1919 // MASM parsers handle strings in expressions as constants. ----
1920 SMLoc ValueLoc = Tok.getLoc(); 0
1921 int64_t Res; ----
1922 const MCExpr *Val; ----
1923 if (Parser.parsePrimaryExpr(Val, End, nullptr)) 0
1924 return true; 0
1925 UpdateLocLex = false; 0
1926 if (!Val->evaluateAsAbsolute(Res, getStreamer().getAssemblerPtr())) 0
1927 return Error(ValueLoc, "expected absolute value"); 0
1928 if (SM.onInteger(Res, ErrMsg)) 0
1929 return Error(ValueLoc, ErrMsg); 0
1930 break; 0
1931 } ----
1932 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1933 } ----
1934 case AsmToken::At: ----
1935 case AsmToken::Identifier: { ----
1936 SMLoc IdentLoc = Tok.getLoc(); 0
1937 StringRef Identifier = Tok.getString(); 0
1938 UpdateLocLex = false; 0
1939 if (Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
1940 size_t DotOffset = Identifier.find_first_of('.'); 0
1941 if (DotOffset != StringRef::npos) { 0
1942 consumeToken(); 0
1943 StringRef LHS = Identifier.slice(0, DotOffset); 0
1944 StringRef Dot = Identifier.slice(DotOffset, DotOffset + 1); 0
1945 StringRef RHS = Identifier.slice(DotOffset + 1, StringRef::npos); 0
1946 if (!RHS.empty()) { 0
1947 getLexer().UnLex(AsmToken(AsmToken::Identifier, RHS)); 0
1948 } ----
1949 getLexer().UnLex(AsmToken(AsmToken::Dot, Dot)); 0
1950 if (!LHS.empty()) { 0
1951 getLexer().UnLex(AsmToken(AsmToken::Identifier, LHS)); 0
1952 } ----
1953 break; 0
1954 } ----
1955 } ----
1956 // (MASM only) PTR operator ----
1957 if (Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
1958 const AsmToken &NextTok = getLexer().peekTok(); 0
1959 if (NextTok.is(AsmToken::Identifier) && 0
1960 NextTok.getIdentifier().equals_insensitive("ptr")) { 0
1961 AsmTypeInfo Info; 0
1962 if (Parser.lookUpType(Identifier, Info)) 0
1963 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "unknown type"); 0
1964 SM.onCast(Info); 0
1965 // Eat type and PTR. ----
1966 consumeToken(); 0
1967 End = consumeToken(); 0
1968 break; 0
1969 } ----
1970 } 0
1971 // Register, or (MASM only) . ----
1972 MCRegister Reg; 0
1973 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) { 0
1974 if (!ParseRegister(Reg, IdentLoc, End, /*RestoreOnFailure=*/true)) { 0
1975 if (SM.onRegister(Reg, ErrMsg)) 0
1976 return Error(IdentLoc, ErrMsg); 0
1977 break; 0
1978 } ----
1979 if (Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
1980 const std::pair IDField = ----
1981 Tok.getString().split('.'); 0
1982 const StringRef ID = IDField.first, Field = IDField.second; 0
1983 SMLoc IDEndLoc = SMLoc::getFromPointer(ID.data() + ID.size()); 0
1984 if (!Field.empty() && 0
1985 !MatchRegisterByName(Reg, ID, IdentLoc, IDEndLoc)) { 0
1986 if (SM.onRegister(Reg, ErrMsg)) 0
1987 return Error(IdentLoc, ErrMsg); 0
1988 ----
1989 AsmFieldInfo Info; 0
1990 SMLoc FieldStartLoc = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Field.data()); 0
1991 if (Parser.lookUpField(Field, Info)) 0
1992 return Error(FieldStartLoc, "unknown offset"); 0
1993 else if (SM.onPlus(ErrMsg)) 0
1994 return Error(getTok().getLoc(), ErrMsg); 0
1995 else if (SM.onInteger(Info.Offset, ErrMsg)) 0
1996 return Error(IdentLoc, ErrMsg); 0
1997 SM.setTypeInfo(Info.Type); 0
1998 ----
1999 End = consumeToken(); 0
2000 break; 0
2001 } ----
2002 } ----
2003 } ----
2004 // Operator synonymous ("not", "or" etc.) ----
2005 bool ParseError = false; 0
2006 if (ParseIntelNamedOperator(Identifier, SM, ParseError, End)) { 0
2007 if (ParseError) 0
2008 return true; 0
2009 break; 0
2010 } ----
2011 if (Parser.isParsingMasm() && 0
2012 ParseMasmNamedOperator(Identifier, SM, ParseError, End)) { 0
2013 if (ParseError) 0
2014 return true; 0
2015 break; 0
2016 } ----
2017 // Symbol reference, when parsing assembly content ----
2018 InlineAsmIdentifierInfo Info; 0
2019 AsmFieldInfo FieldInfo; 0
2020 const MCExpr *Val; ----
2021 if (isParsingMSInlineAsm() || Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
2022 // MS Dot Operator expression ----
2023 if (Identifier.count('.') && 0
2024 (PrevTK == AsmToken::RBrac || PrevTK == AsmToken::RParen)) { 0
2025 if (ParseIntelDotOperator(SM, End)) 0
2026 return true; 0
2027 break; 0
2028 } ----
2029 } ----
2030 if (isParsingMSInlineAsm()) { 0
2031 // MS InlineAsm operators (TYPE/LENGTH/SIZE) ----
2032 if (unsigned OpKind = IdentifyIntelInlineAsmOperator(Identifier)) { 0
2033 if (int64_t Val = ParseIntelInlineAsmOperator(OpKind)) { 0
2034 if (SM.onInteger(Val, ErrMsg)) 0
2035 return Error(IdentLoc, ErrMsg); 0
2036 } else { ----
2037 return true; 0
2038 } ----
2039 break; 0
2040 } ----
2041 // MS InlineAsm identifier ----
2042 // Call parseIdentifier() to combine @ with the identifier behind it. ----
2043 if (TK == AsmToken::At && Parser.parseIdentifier(Identifier)) 0
2044 return Error(IdentLoc, "expected identifier"); 0
2045 if (ParseIntelInlineAsmIdentifier(Val, Identifier, Info, false, End)) 0
2046 return true; 0
2047 else if (SM.onIdentifierExpr(Val, Identifier, Info, FieldInfo.Type, 0
2048 true, ErrMsg)) ----
2049 return Error(IdentLoc, ErrMsg); 0
2050 break; 0
2051 } ----
2052 if (Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
2053 if (unsigned OpKind = IdentifyMasmOperator(Identifier)) { 0
2054 int64_t Val; ----
2055 if (ParseMasmOperator(OpKind, Val)) 0
2056 return true; 0
2057 if (SM.onInteger(Val, ErrMsg)) 0
2058 return Error(IdentLoc, ErrMsg); 0
2059 break; 0
2060 } ----
2061 if (!getParser().lookUpType(Identifier, FieldInfo.Type)) { 0
2062 // Field offset immediate; . ----
2063 Lex(); // eat type 0
2064 bool EndDot = parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Dot); 0
2065 while (EndDot || (getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier) && 0
2066 getTok().getString().startswith("."))) { 0
2067 getParser().parseIdentifier(Identifier); 0
2068 if (!EndDot) 0
2069 Identifier.consume_front("."); 0
2070 EndDot = Identifier.consume_back("."); 0
2071 if (getParser().lookUpField(FieldInfo.Type.Name, Identifier, 0
2072 FieldInfo)) { ----
2073 SMLoc IDEnd = ----
2074 SMLoc::getFromPointer(Identifier.data() + Identifier.size()); 0
2075 return Error(IdentLoc, "Unable to lookup field reference!", 0
2076 SMRange(IdentLoc, IDEnd)); 0
2077 } ----
2078 if (!EndDot) 0
2079 EndDot = parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Dot); 0
2080 } ----
2081 if (SM.onInteger(FieldInfo.Offset, ErrMsg)) 0
2082 return Error(IdentLoc, ErrMsg); 0
2083 break; 0
2084 } ----
2085 } ----
2086 if (getParser().parsePrimaryExpr(Val, End, &FieldInfo.Type)) { 0
2087 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Unexpected identifier!"); 0
2088 } else if (SM.onIdentifierExpr(Val, Identifier, Info, FieldInfo.Type, 0
2089 false, ErrMsg)) { ----
2090 return Error(IdentLoc, ErrMsg); 0
2091 } ----
2092 break; 0
2093 } ----
2094 case AsmToken::Integer: { 0
2095 // Look for 'b' or 'f' following an Integer as a directional label ----
2096 SMLoc Loc = getTok().getLoc(); 0
2097 int64_t IntVal = getTok().getIntVal(); 0
2098 End = consumeToken(); 0
2099 UpdateLocLex = false; 0
2100 if (getLexer().getKind() == AsmToken::Identifier) { 0
2101 StringRef IDVal = getTok().getString(); 0
2102 if (IDVal == "f" || IDVal == "b") { 0
2103 MCSymbol *Sym = ----
2104 getContext().getDirectionalLocalSymbol(IntVal, IDVal == "b"); 0
2105 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None; 0
2106 const MCExpr *Val = ----
2107 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, Variant, getContext()); 0
2108 if (IDVal == "b" && Sym->isUndefined()) 0
2109 return Error(Loc, "invalid reference to undefined symbol"); 0
2110 StringRef Identifier = Sym->getName(); 0
2111 InlineAsmIdentifierInfo Info; 0
2112 AsmTypeInfo Type; 0
2113 if (SM.onIdentifierExpr(Val, Identifier, Info, Type, 0
2114 isParsingMSInlineAsm(), ErrMsg)) 0
2115 return Error(Loc, ErrMsg); 0
2116 End = consumeToken(); 0
2117 } else { ----
2118 if (SM.onInteger(IntVal, ErrMsg)) 0
2119 return Error(Loc, ErrMsg); 0
2120 } ----
2121 } else { ----
2122 if (SM.onInteger(IntVal, ErrMsg)) 0
2123 return Error(Loc, ErrMsg); 0
2124 } ----
2125 break; 0
2126 } ----
2127 case AsmToken::Plus: 0
2128 if (SM.onPlus(ErrMsg)) 0
2129 return Error(getTok().getLoc(), ErrMsg); 0
2130 break; 0
2131 case AsmToken::Minus: 0
2132 if (SM.onMinus(ErrMsg)) 0
2133 return Error(getTok().getLoc(), ErrMsg); 0
2134 break; 0
2135 case AsmToken::Tilde: SM.onNot(); break; 0
2136 case AsmToken::Star: SM.onStar(); break; 0
2137 case AsmToken::Slash: SM.onDivide(); break; 0
2138 case AsmToken::Percent: SM.onMod(); break; 0
2139 case AsmToken::Pipe: SM.onOr(); break; 0
2140 case AsmToken::Caret: SM.onXor(); break; 0
2141 case AsmToken::Amp: SM.onAnd(); break; 0
2142 case AsmToken::LessLess: 0
2143 SM.onLShift(); break; 0
2144 case AsmToken::GreaterGreater: 0
2145 SM.onRShift(); break; 0
2146 case AsmToken::LBrac: 0
2147 if (SM.onLBrac()) 0
2148 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "unexpected bracket encountered"); 0
2149 tryParseOperandIdx(PrevTK, SM); 0
2150 break; 0
2151 case AsmToken::RBrac: 0
2152 if (SM.onRBrac(ErrMsg)) { 0
2153 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), ErrMsg); 0
2154 } ----
2155 break; 0
2156 case AsmToken::LParen: SM.onLParen(); break; 0
2157 case AsmToken::RParen: SM.onRParen(); break; 0
2158 } ----
2159 if (SM.hadError()) 0
2160 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "unknown token in expression"); 0
2161 ----
2162 if (!Done && UpdateLocLex) 0
2163 End = consumeToken(); 0
2164 ----
2165 PrevTK = TK; 0
2166 } ----
2167 return false; 0
2168 } ----
2169 ----
2170 void X86AsmParser::RewriteIntelExpression(IntelExprStateMachine &SM, 0
2171 SMLoc Start, SMLoc End) { ----
2172 SMLoc Loc = Start; 0
2173 unsigned ExprLen = End.getPointer() - Start.getPointer(); 0
2174 // Skip everything before a symbol displacement (if we have one) ----
2175 if (SM.getSym() && !SM.isOffsetOperator()) { 0
2176 StringRef SymName = SM.getSymName(); 0
2177 if (unsigned Len = SymName.data() - Start.getPointer()) 0
2178 InstInfo->AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_Skip, Start, Len); 0
2179 Loc = SMLoc::getFromPointer(SymName.data() + SymName.size()); 0
2180 ExprLen = End.getPointer() - (SymName.data() + SymName.size()); 0
2181 // If we have only a symbol than there's no need for complex rewrite, ----
2182 // simply skip everything after it ----
2183 if (!(SM.getBaseReg() || SM.getIndexReg() || SM.getImm())) { 0
2184 if (ExprLen) 0
2185 InstInfo->AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_Skip, Loc, ExprLen); 0
2186 return; 0
2187 } ----
2188 } ----
2189 // Build an Intel Expression rewrite ----
2190 StringRef BaseRegStr; 0
2191 StringRef IndexRegStr; 0
2192 StringRef OffsetNameStr; 0
2193 if (SM.getBaseReg()) 0
2194 BaseRegStr = X86IntelInstPrinter::getRegisterName(SM.getBaseReg()); 0
2195 if (SM.getIndexReg()) 0
2196 IndexRegStr = X86IntelInstPrinter::getRegisterName(SM.getIndexReg()); 0
2197 if (SM.isOffsetOperator()) 0
2198 OffsetNameStr = SM.getSymName(); 0
2199 // Emit it ----
2200 IntelExpr Expr(BaseRegStr, IndexRegStr, SM.getScale(), OffsetNameStr, ----
2201 SM.getImm(), SM.isMemExpr()); 0
2202 InstInfo->AsmRewrites->emplace_back(Loc, ExprLen, Expr); 0
2203 } ----

2205 // Inline assembly may use variable names with namespace alias qualifiers. ----
2206 bool X86AsmParser::ParseIntelInlineAsmIdentifier( 0
2207 const MCExpr *&Val, StringRef &Identifier, InlineAsmIdentifierInfo &Info, ----
2208 bool IsUnevaluatedOperand, SMLoc &End, bool IsParsingOffsetOperator) { ----
2209 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2210 assert(isParsingMSInlineAsm() && "Expected to be parsing inline assembly."); 0
2211 Val = nullptr; 0
2212 ----
2213 StringRef LineBuf(Identifier.data()); 0
2214 SemaCallback->LookupInlineAsmIdentifier(LineBuf, Info, IsUnevaluatedOperand); 0
2215 ----
2216 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
2217 SMLoc Loc = Tok.getLoc(); 0
2218 ----
2219 // Advance the token stream until the end of the current token is ----
2220 // after the end of what the frontend claimed. ----
2221 const char *EndPtr = Tok.getLoc().getPointer() + LineBuf.size(); 0
2222 do { ----
2223 End = Tok.getEndLoc(); 0
2224 getLexer().Lex(); 0
2225 } while (End.getPointer() < EndPtr); 0
2226 Identifier = LineBuf; 0
2227 ----
2228 // The frontend should end parsing on an assembler token boundary, unless it ----
2229 // failed parsing. ----
2230 assert((End.getPointer() == EndPtr || 0
2231 Info.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_Invalid)) && ----
2232 "frontend claimed part of a token?"); ----
2233 ----
2234 // If the identifier lookup was unsuccessful, assume that we are dealing with ----
2235 // a label. ----
2236 if (Info.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_Invalid)) { 0
2237 StringRef InternalName = ----
2238 SemaCallback->LookupInlineAsmLabel(Identifier, getSourceManager(), 0
2239 Loc, false); ----
2240 assert(InternalName.size() && "We should have an internal name here."); 0
2241 // Push a rewrite for replacing the identifier name with the internal name, ----
2242 // unless we are parsing the operand of an offset operator ----
2243 if (!IsParsingOffsetOperator) 0
2244 InstInfo->AsmRewrites->emplace_back(AOK_Label, Loc, Identifier.size(), 0
2245 InternalName); ----
2246 else ----
2247 Identifier = InternalName; 0
2248 } else if (Info.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_EnumVal)) 0
2249 return false; 0
2250 // Create the symbol reference. ----
2251 MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Identifier); 0
2252 MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind Variant = MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None; 0
2253 Val = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sym, Variant, getParser().getContext()); 0
2254 return false; 0
2255 } ----
2256 ----
2257 //ParseRoundingModeOp - Parse AVX-512 rounding mode operand ----
2258 bool X86AsmParser::ParseRoundingModeOp(SMLoc Start, OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2259 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2260 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
2261 // Eat "{" and mark the current place. ----
2262 const SMLoc consumedToken = consumeToken(); 0
2263 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2264 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Expected an identifier after {"); 0
2265 if (Tok.getIdentifier().startswith("r")){ 0
2266 int rndMode = StringSwitch(Tok.getIdentifier()) 0
2267 .Case("rn", X86::STATIC_ROUNDING::TO_NEAREST_INT) 0
2268 .Case("rd", X86::STATIC_ROUNDING::TO_NEG_INF) 0
2269 .Case("ru", X86::STATIC_ROUNDING::TO_POS_INF) 0
2270 .Case("rz", X86::STATIC_ROUNDING::TO_ZERO) 0
2271 .Default(-1); 0
2272 if (-1 == rndMode) 0
2273 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Invalid rounding mode."); 0
2274 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "r*" of r*-sae 0
2275 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::Minus)) 0
2276 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Expected - at this point"); 0
2277 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "-" 0
2278 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the sae 0
2279 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::RCurly)) 0
2280 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Expected } at this point"); 0
2281 SMLoc End = Tok.getEndLoc(); 0
2282 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "}" 0
2283 const MCExpr *RndModeOp = ----
2284 MCConstantExpr::create(rndMode, Parser.getContext()); 0
2285 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateImm(RndModeOp, Start, End)); 0
2286 return false; 0
2287 } ----
2288 if(Tok.getIdentifier().equals("sae")){ 0
2289 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the sae 0
2290 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::RCurly)) 0
2291 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Expected } at this point"); 0
2292 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "}" 0
2293 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateToken("{sae}", consumedToken)); 0
2294 return false; 0
2295 } ----
2296 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "unknown token in expression"); 0
2297 } ----
2298 ----
2299 /// Parse the '.' operator. ----
2300 bool X86AsmParser::ParseIntelDotOperator(IntelExprStateMachine &SM, 0
2301 SMLoc &End) { ----
2302 const AsmToken &Tok = getTok(); 0
2303 AsmFieldInfo Info; 0
2304 ----
2305 // Drop the optional '.'. ----
2306 StringRef DotDispStr = Tok.getString(); 0
2307 if (DotDispStr.startswith(".")) 0
2308 DotDispStr = DotDispStr.drop_front(1); 0
2309 StringRef TrailingDot; 0
2310 ----
2311 // .Imm gets lexed as a real. ----
2312 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Real)) { 0
2313 APInt DotDisp; 0
2314 if (DotDispStr.getAsInteger(10, DotDisp)) 0
2315 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Unexpected offset"); 0
2316 Info.Offset = DotDisp.getZExtValue(); 0
2317 } else if ((isParsingMSInlineAsm() || getParser().isParsingMasm()) && 0
2318 Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) { 0
2319 if (DotDispStr.endswith(".")) { 0
2320 TrailingDot = DotDispStr.substr(DotDispStr.size() - 1); 0
2321 DotDispStr = DotDispStr.drop_back(1); 0
2322 } ----
2323 const std::pair BaseMember = DotDispStr.split('.'); 0
2324 const StringRef Base = BaseMember.first, Member = BaseMember.second; 0
2325 if (getParser().lookUpField(SM.getType(), DotDispStr, Info) && 0
2326 getParser().lookUpField(SM.getSymName(), DotDispStr, Info) && 0
2327 getParser().lookUpField(DotDispStr, Info) && 0
2328 (!SemaCallback || 0
2329 SemaCallback->LookupInlineAsmField(Base, Member, Info.Offset))) 0
2330 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Unable to lookup field reference!"); 0
2331 } else { ----
2332 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Unexpected token type!"); 0
2333 } ----
2334 ----
2335 // Eat the DotExpression and update End ----
2336 End = SMLoc::getFromPointer(DotDispStr.data()); 0
2337 const char *DotExprEndLoc = DotDispStr.data() + DotDispStr.size(); 0
2338 while (Tok.getLoc().getPointer() < DotExprEndLoc) 0
2339 Lex(); 0
2340 if (!TrailingDot.empty()) 0
2341 getLexer().UnLex(AsmToken(AsmToken::Dot, TrailingDot)); 0
2342 SM.addImm(Info.Offset); 0
2343 SM.setTypeInfo(Info.Type); 0
2344 return false; 0
2345 } ----
2346 ----
2347 /// Parse the 'offset' operator. ----
2348 /// This operator is used to specify the location of a given operand ----
2349 bool X86AsmParser::ParseIntelOffsetOperator(const MCExpr *&Val, StringRef &ID, 0
2350 InlineAsmIdentifierInfo &Info, ----
2351 SMLoc &End) { ----
2352 // Eat offset, mark start of identifier. ----
2353 SMLoc Start = Lex().getLoc(); 0
2354 ID = getTok().getString(); 0
2355 if (!isParsingMSInlineAsm()) { 0
2356 if ((getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier) && 0
2357 getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String)) || 0
2358 getParser().parsePrimaryExpr(Val, End, nullptr)) 0
2359 return Error(Start, "unexpected token!"); 0
2360 } else if (ParseIntelInlineAsmIdentifier(Val, ID, Info, false, End, true)) { 0
2361 return Error(Start, "unable to lookup expression"); 0
2362 } else if (Info.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_EnumVal)) { 0
2363 return Error(Start, "offset operator cannot yet handle constants"); 0
2364 } ----
2365 return false; 0
2366 } ----

2368 // Query a candidate string for being an Intel assembly operator ----
2369 // Report back its kind, or IOK_INVALID if does not evaluated as a known one ----
2370 unsigned X86AsmParser::IdentifyIntelInlineAsmOperator(StringRef Name) { 0
2371 return StringSwitch(Name) 0
2372 .Cases("TYPE","type",IOK_TYPE) 0
2373 .Cases("SIZE","size",IOK_SIZE) 0
2374 .Cases("LENGTH","length",IOK_LENGTH) 0
2375 .Default(IOK_INVALID); 0
2376 } ----
2377 ----
2378 /// Parse the 'LENGTH', 'TYPE' and 'SIZE' operators. The LENGTH operator ----
2379 /// returns the number of elements in an array. It returns the value 1 for ----
2380 /// non-array variables. The SIZE operator returns the size of a C or C++ ----
2381 /// variable. A variable's size is the product of its LENGTH and TYPE. The ----
2382 /// TYPE operator returns the size of a C or C++ type or variable. If the ----
2383 /// variable is an array, TYPE returns the size of a single element. ----
2384 unsigned X86AsmParser::ParseIntelInlineAsmOperator(unsigned OpKind) { 0
2385 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2386 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
2387 Parser.Lex(); // Eat operator. 0
2388 ----
2389 const MCExpr *Val = nullptr; 0
2390 InlineAsmIdentifierInfo Info; 0
2391 SMLoc Start = Tok.getLoc(), End; 0
2392 StringRef Identifier = Tok.getString(); 0
2393 if (ParseIntelInlineAsmIdentifier(Val, Identifier, Info, 0
2394 /*IsUnevaluatedOperand=*/true, End)) ----
2395 return 0; 0
2396 ----
2397 if (!Info.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_Var)) { 0
2398 Error(Start, "unable to lookup expression"); 0
2399 return 0; 0
2400 } ----
2401 ----
2402 unsigned CVal = 0; 0
2403 switch(OpKind) { 0
2404 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected operand kind!"); 0
2405 case IOK_LENGTH: CVal = Info.Var.Length; break; 0
2406 case IOK_SIZE: CVal = Info.Var.Size; break; 0
2407 case IOK_TYPE: CVal = Info.Var.Type; break; 0
2408 } ----
2409 ----
2410 return CVal; 0
2411 } ----
2412 ----
2413 // Query a candidate string for being an Intel assembly operator ----
2414 // Report back its kind, or IOK_INVALID if does not evaluated as a known one ----
2415 unsigned X86AsmParser::IdentifyMasmOperator(StringRef Name) { 0
2416 return StringSwitch(Name.lower()) 0
2417 .Case("type", MOK_TYPE) 0
2418 .Cases("size", "sizeof", MOK_SIZEOF) 0
2419 .Cases("length", "lengthof", MOK_LENGTHOF) 0
2420 .Default(MOK_INVALID); 0
2421 } ----
2422 ----
2423 /// Parse the 'LENGTHOF', 'SIZEOF', and 'TYPE' operators. The LENGTHOF operator ----
2424 /// returns the number of elements in an array. It returns the value 1 for ----
2425 /// non-array variables. The SIZEOF operator returns the size of a type or ----
2426 /// variable in bytes. A variable's size is the product of its LENGTH and TYPE. ----
2427 /// The TYPE operator returns the size of a variable. If the variable is an ----
2428 /// array, TYPE returns the size of a single element. ----
2429 bool X86AsmParser::ParseMasmOperator(unsigned OpKind, int64_t &Val) { 0
2430 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2431 SMLoc OpLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2432 Parser.Lex(); // Eat operator. 0
2433 ----
2434 Val = 0; 0
2435 if (OpKind == MOK_SIZEOF || OpKind == MOK_TYPE) { 0
2436 // Check for SIZEOF() and TYPE(). ----
2437 bool InParens = Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::LParen); 0
2438 const AsmToken &IDTok = InParens ? getLexer().peekTok() : Parser.getTok(); 0
2439 AsmTypeInfo Type; 0
2440 if (IDTok.is(AsmToken::Identifier) && 0
2441 !Parser.lookUpType(IDTok.getIdentifier(), Type)) { 0
2442 Val = Type.Size; 0
2443 ----
2444 // Eat tokens. ----
2445 if (InParens) 0
2446 parseToken(AsmToken::LParen); 0
2447 parseToken(AsmToken::Identifier); 0
2448 if (InParens) 0
2449 parseToken(AsmToken::RParen); 0
2450 } ----
2451 } 0
2452 ----
2453 if (!Val) { 0
2454 IntelExprStateMachine SM; 0
2455 SMLoc End, Start = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2456 if (ParseIntelExpression(SM, End)) 0
2457 return true; 0
2458 ----
2459 switch (OpKind) { 0
2460 default: 0
2461 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected operand kind!"); 0
2462 case MOK_SIZEOF: 0
2463 Val = SM.getSize(); 0
2464 break; 0
2465 case MOK_LENGTHOF: 0
2466 Val = SM.getLength(); 0
2467 break; 0
2468 case MOK_TYPE: 0
2469 Val = SM.getElementSize(); 0
2470 break; 0
2471 } ----
2472 ----
2473 if (!Val) 0
2474 return Error(OpLoc, "expression has unknown type", SMRange(Start, End)); 0
2475 } 0
2476 ----
2477 return false; 0
2478 } ----
2479 ----
2480 bool X86AsmParser::ParseIntelMemoryOperandSize(unsigned &Size) { 0
2481 Size = StringSwitch(getTok().getString()) 0
2482 .Cases("BYTE", "byte", 8) 0
2483 .Cases("WORD", "word", 16) 0
2484 .Cases("DWORD", "dword", 32) 0
2485 .Cases("FLOAT", "float", 32) 0
2486 .Cases("LONG", "long", 32) 0
2487 .Cases("FWORD", "fword", 48) 0
2488 .Cases("DOUBLE", "double", 64) 0
2489 .Cases("QWORD", "qword", 64) 0
2490 .Cases("MMWORD","mmword", 64) 0
2491 .Cases("XWORD", "xword", 80) 0
2492 .Cases("TBYTE", "tbyte", 80) 0
2493 .Cases("XMMWORD", "xmmword", 128) 0
2494 .Cases("YMMWORD", "ymmword", 256) 0
2495 .Cases("ZMMWORD", "zmmword", 512) 0
2496 .Default(0); 0
2497 if (Size) { 0
2498 const AsmToken &Tok = Lex(); // Eat operand size (e.g., byte, word). 0
2499 if (!(Tok.getString().equals("PTR") || Tok.getString().equals("ptr"))) 0
2500 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "Expected 'PTR' or 'ptr' token!"); 0
2501 Lex(); // Eat ptr. 0
2502 } ----
2503 return false; 0
2504 } ----
2505 ----
2506 bool X86AsmParser::parseIntelOperand(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Name) { 0
2507 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2508 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
2509 SMLoc Start, End; 0
2510 ----
2511 // Parse optional Size directive. ----
2512 unsigned Size; ----
2513 if (ParseIntelMemoryOperandSize(Size)) 0
2514 return true; 0
2515 bool PtrInOperand = bool(Size); 0
2516 ----
2517 Start = Tok.getLoc(); 0
2518 ----
2519 // Rounding mode operand. ----
2520 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LCurly)) 0
2521 return ParseRoundingModeOp(Start, Operands); 0
2522 ----
2523 // Register operand. ----
2524 MCRegister RegNo; 0
2525 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier) && !parseRegister(RegNo, Start, End)) { 0
2526 if (RegNo == X86::RIP) 0
2527 return Error(Start, "rip can only be used as a base register"); 0
2528 // A Register followed by ':' is considered a segment override ----
2529 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Colon)) { 0
2530 if (PtrInOperand) 0
2531 return Error(Start, "expected memory operand after 'ptr', " 0
2532 "found register operand instead"); 0
2533 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateReg(RegNo, Start, End)); 0
2534 return false; 0
2535 } ----
2536 // An alleged segment override. check if we have a valid segment register ----
2537 if (!X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::SEGMENT_REGRegClassID].contains(RegNo)) 0
2538 return Error(Start, "invalid segment register"); 0
2539 // Eat ':' and update Start location ----
2540 Start = Lex().getLoc(); 0
2541 } ----
2542 ----
2543 // Immediates and Memory ----
2544 IntelExprStateMachine SM; 0
2545 if (ParseIntelExpression(SM, End)) 0
2546 return true; 0
2547 ----
2548 if (isParsingMSInlineAsm()) 0
2549 RewriteIntelExpression(SM, Start, Tok.getLoc()); 0
2550 ----
2551 int64_t Imm = SM.getImm(); 0
2552 const MCExpr *Disp = SM.getSym(); 0
2553 const MCExpr *ImmDisp = MCConstantExpr::create(Imm, getContext()); 0
2554 if (Disp && Imm) 0
2555 Disp = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(Disp, ImmDisp, getContext()); 0
2556 if (!Disp) 0
2557 Disp = ImmDisp; 0
2558 ----
2559 // RegNo != 0 specifies a valid segment register, ----
2560 // and we are parsing a segment override ----
2561 if (!SM.isMemExpr() && !RegNo) { 0
2562 if (isParsingMSInlineAsm() && SM.isOffsetOperator()) { 0
2563 const InlineAsmIdentifierInfo &Info = SM.getIdentifierInfo(); 0
2564 if (Info.isKind(InlineAsmIdentifierInfo::IK_Var)) { 0
2565 // Disp includes the address of a variable; make sure this is recorded ----
2566 // for later handling. ----
2567 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateImm(Disp, Start, End, 0
2568 SM.getSymName(), Info.Var.Decl, 0
2569 Info.Var.IsGlobalLV)); 0
2570 return false; 0
2571 } ----
2572 } ----
2573 ----
2574 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateImm(Disp, Start, End)); 0
2575 return false; 0
2576 } ----
2577 ----
2578 StringRef ErrMsg; 0
2579 unsigned BaseReg = SM.getBaseReg(); 0
2580 unsigned IndexReg = SM.getIndexReg(); 0
2581 if (IndexReg && BaseReg == X86::RIP) 0
2582 BaseReg = 0; 0
2583 unsigned Scale = SM.getScale(); 0
2584 if (!PtrInOperand) 0
2585 Size = SM.getElementSize() << 3; 0
2586 ----
2587 if (Scale == 0 && BaseReg != X86::ESP && BaseReg != X86::RSP && 0
2588 (IndexReg == X86::ESP || IndexReg == X86::RSP)) 0
2589 std::swap(BaseReg, IndexReg); 0
2590 ----
2591 // If BaseReg is a vector register and IndexReg is not, swap them unless ----
2592 // Scale was specified in which case it would be an error. ----
2593 if (Scale == 0 && 0
2594 !(X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR128XRegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
2595 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR256XRegClassID].contains(IndexReg) || 0
2596 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR512RegClassID].contains(IndexReg)) && 0
2597 (X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR128XRegClassID].contains(BaseReg) || 0
2598 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR256XRegClassID].contains(BaseReg) || 0
2599 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VR512RegClassID].contains(BaseReg))) 0
2600 std::swap(BaseReg, IndexReg); 0
2601 ----
2602 if (Scale != 0 && 0
2603 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::GR16RegClassID].contains(IndexReg)) 0
2604 return Error(Start, "16-bit addresses cannot have a scale"); 0
2605 ----
2606 // If there was no explicit scale specified, change it to 1. ----
2607 if (Scale == 0) 0
2608 Scale = 1; 0
2609 ----
2610 // If this is a 16-bit addressing mode with the base and index in the wrong ----
2611 // order, swap them so CheckBaseRegAndIndexRegAndScale doesn't fail. It is ----
2612 // shared with att syntax where order matters. ----
2613 if ((BaseReg == X86::SI || BaseReg == X86::DI) && 0
2614 (IndexReg == X86::BX || IndexReg == X86::BP)) 0
2615 std::swap(BaseReg, IndexReg); 0
2616 ----
2617 if ((BaseReg || IndexReg) && 0
2618 CheckBaseRegAndIndexRegAndScale(BaseReg, IndexReg, Scale, is64BitMode(), 0
2619 ErrMsg)) ----
2620 return Error(Start, ErrMsg); 0
2621 if (isParsingMSInlineAsm()) 0
2622 return CreateMemForMSInlineAsm(RegNo, Disp, BaseReg, IndexReg, Scale, Start, 0
2623 End, Size, SM.getSymName(), ----
2624 SM.getIdentifierInfo(), Operands); 0
2625 ----
2626 // When parsing x64 MS-style assembly, all non-absolute references to a named ----
2627 // variable default to RIP-relative. ----
2628 unsigned DefaultBaseReg = X86::NoRegister; 0
2629 bool MaybeDirectBranchDest = true; 0
2630 ----
2631 bool IsUnconditionalBranch = ----
2632 Name.equals_insensitive("jmp") || Name.equals_insensitive("call"); 0
2633 if (Parser.isParsingMasm()) { 0
2634 if (is64BitMode() && SM.getElementSize() > 0) { 0
2635 DefaultBaseReg = X86::RIP; 0
2636 } ----
2637 if (IsUnconditionalBranch) { 0
2638 if (PtrInOperand) { 0
2639 MaybeDirectBranchDest = false; 0
2640 if (is64BitMode()) 0
2641 DefaultBaseReg = X86::RIP; 0
2642 } else if (!BaseReg && !IndexReg && Disp && 0
2643 Disp->getKind() == MCExpr::SymbolRef) { 0
2644 if (is64BitMode()) { 0
2645 if (SM.getSize() == 8) { 0
2646 MaybeDirectBranchDest = false; 0
2647 DefaultBaseReg = X86::RIP; 0
2648 } ----
2649 } else { ----
2650 if (SM.getSize() == 4 || SM.getSize() == 2) 0
2651 MaybeDirectBranchDest = false; 0
2652 } ----
2653 } ----
2654 } ----
2655 } else if (IsUnconditionalBranch) { 0
2656 // Treat `call [offset fn_ref]` (or `jmp`) syntax as an error. ----
2657 if (!PtrInOperand && SM.isOffsetOperator()) 0
2658 return Error( 0
2659 Start, "`OFFSET` operator cannot be used in an unconditional branch"); 0
2660 if (PtrInOperand || SM.isBracketUsed()) 0
2661 MaybeDirectBranchDest = false; 0
2662 } ----
2663 ----
2664 if ((BaseReg || IndexReg || RegNo || DefaultBaseReg != X86::NoRegister)) 0
2665 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateMem( 0
2666 getPointerWidth(), RegNo, Disp, BaseReg, IndexReg, Scale, Start, End, ----
2667 Size, DefaultBaseReg, /*SymName=*/StringRef(), /*OpDecl=*/nullptr, ----
2668 /*FrontendSize=*/0, /*UseUpRegs=*/false, MaybeDirectBranchDest)); ----
2669 else ----
2670 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateMem( 0
2671 getPointerWidth(), Disp, Start, End, Size, /*SymName=*/StringRef(), ----
2672 /*OpDecl=*/nullptr, /*FrontendSize=*/0, /*UseUpRegs=*/false, ----
2673 MaybeDirectBranchDest)); ----
2674 return false; 0
2675 } 0
2676 ----
2677 bool X86AsmParser::parseATTOperand(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2678 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2679 switch (getLexer().getKind()) { 0
2680 case AsmToken::Dollar: { 0
2681 // $42 or $ID -> immediate. ----
2682 SMLoc Start = Parser.getTok().getLoc(), End; 0
2683 Parser.Lex(); 0
2684 const MCExpr *Val; ----
2685 // This is an immediate, so we should not parse a register. Do a precheck ----
2686 // for '%' to supercede intra-register parse errors. ----
2687 SMLoc L = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2688 if (check(getLexer().is(AsmToken::Percent), L, 0
2689 "expected immediate expression") || 0
2690 getParser().parseExpression(Val, End) || 0
2691 check(isa(Val), L, "expected immediate expression")) 0
2692 return true; 0
2693 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateImm(Val, Start, End)); 0
2694 return false; 0
2695 } ----
2696 case AsmToken::LCurly: { 0
2697 SMLoc Start = Parser.getTok().getLoc(); 0
2698 return ParseRoundingModeOp(Start, Operands); 0
2699 } ----
2700 default: { 0
2701 // This a memory operand or a register. We have some parsing complications ----
2702 // as a '(' may be part of an immediate expression or the addressing mode ----
2703 // block. This is complicated by the fact that an assembler-level variable ----
2704 // may refer either to a register or an immediate expression. ----
2705 ----
2706 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc(), EndLoc; 0
2707 const MCExpr *Expr = nullptr; 0
2708 unsigned Reg = 0; 0
2709 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::LParen)) { 0
2710 // No '(' so this is either a displacement expression or a register. ----
2711 if (Parser.parseExpression(Expr, EndLoc)) 0
2712 return true; 0
2713 if (auto *RE = dyn_cast(Expr)) { 0
2714 // Segment Register. Reset Expr and copy value to register. ----
2715 Expr = nullptr; 0
2716 Reg = RE->getRegNo(); 0
2717 ----
2718 // Check the register. ----
2719 if (Reg == X86::EIZ || Reg == X86::RIZ) 0
2720 return Error( 0
2721 Loc, "%eiz and %riz can only be used as index registers", ----
2722 SMRange(Loc, EndLoc)); 0
2723 if (Reg == X86::RIP) 0
2724 return Error(Loc, "%rip can only be used as a base register", 0
2725 SMRange(Loc, EndLoc)); 0
2726 // Return register that are not segment prefixes immediately. ----
2727 if (!Parser.parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Colon)) { 0
2728 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateReg(Reg, Loc, EndLoc)); 0
2729 return false; 0
2730 } ----
2731 if (!X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::SEGMENT_REGRegClassID].contains(Reg)) 0
2732 return Error(Loc, "invalid segment register"); 0
2733 // Accept a '*' absolute memory reference after the segment. Place it ----
2734 // before the full memory operand. ----
2735 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Star)) 0
2736 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateToken("*", consumeToken())); 0
2737 } ----
2738 } ----
2739 // This is a Memory operand. ----
2740 return ParseMemOperand(Reg, Expr, Loc, EndLoc, Operands); 0
2741 } ----
2742 } ----
2743 } ----
2744 ----
2745 // X86::COND_INVALID if not a recognized condition code or alternate mnemonic, ----
2746 // otherwise the EFLAGS Condition Code enumerator. ----
2747 X86::CondCode X86AsmParser::ParseConditionCode(StringRef CC) { 0
2748 return StringSwitch(CC) 0
2749 .Case("o", X86::COND_O) // Overflow 0
2750 .Case("no", X86::COND_NO) // No Overflow 0
2751 .Cases("b", "nae", X86::COND_B) // Below/Neither Above nor Equal 0
2752 .Cases("ae", "nb", X86::COND_AE) // Above or Equal/Not Below 0
2753 .Cases("e", "z", X86::COND_E) // Equal/Zero 0
2754 .Cases("ne", "nz", X86::COND_NE) // Not Equal/Not Zero 0
2755 .Cases("be", "na", X86::COND_BE) // Below or Equal/Not Above 0
2756 .Cases("a", "nbe", X86::COND_A) // Above/Neither Below nor Equal 0
2757 .Case("s", X86::COND_S) // Sign 0
2758 .Case("ns", X86::COND_NS) // No Sign 0
2759 .Cases("p", "pe", X86::COND_P) // Parity/Parity Even 0
2760 .Cases("np", "po", X86::COND_NP) // No Parity/Parity Odd 0
2761 .Cases("l", "nge", X86::COND_L) // Less/Neither Greater nor Equal 0
2762 .Cases("ge", "nl", X86::COND_GE) // Greater or Equal/Not Less 0
2763 .Cases("le", "ng", X86::COND_LE) // Less or Equal/Not Greater 0
2764 .Cases("g", "nle", X86::COND_G) // Greater/Neither Less nor Equal 0
2765 .Default(X86::COND_INVALID); 0
2766 } ----
2767 ----
2768 // true on failure, false otherwise ----
2769 // If no {z} mark was found - Parser doesn't advance ----
2770 bool X86AsmParser::ParseZ(std::unique_ptr &Z, 0
2771 const SMLoc &StartLoc) { ----
2772 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2773 // Assuming we are just pass the '{' mark, quering the next token ----
2774 // Searched for {z}, but none was found. Return false, as no parsing error was ----
2775 // encountered ----
2776 if (!(getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier) && 0
2777 (getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier() == "z"))) 0
2778 return false; 0
2779 Parser.Lex(); // Eat z 0
2780 // Query and eat the '}' mark ----
2781 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::RCurly)) 0
2782 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(), "Expected } at this point"); 0
2783 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '}' 0
2784 // Assign Z with the {z} mark operand ----
2785 Z = X86Operand::CreateToken("{z}", StartLoc); 0
2786 return false; 0
2787 } ----
2788 ----
2789 // true on failure, false otherwise ----
2790 bool X86AsmParser::HandleAVX512Operand(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
2791 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser(); 0
2792 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LCurly)) { 0
2793 // Eat "{" and mark the current place. ----
2794 const SMLoc consumedToken = consumeToken(); 0
2795 // Distinguish {1to} from {%k}. ----
2796 if(getLexer().is(AsmToken::Integer)) { 0
2797 // Parse memory broadcasting ({1to}). ----
2798 if (getLexer().getTok().getIntVal() != 1) 0
2799 return TokError("Expected 1to at this point"); 0
2800 StringRef Prefix = getLexer().getTok().getString(); 0
2801 Parser.Lex(); // Eat first token of 1to8 0
2802 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) 0
2803 return TokError("Expected 1to at this point"); 0
2804 // Recognize only reasonable suffixes. ----
2805 SmallVector BroadcastVector; 0
2806 StringRef BroadcastString = (Prefix + getLexer().getTok().getIdentifier()) 0
2807 .toStringRef(BroadcastVector); 0
2808 if (!BroadcastString.startswith("1to")) 0
2809 return TokError("Expected 1to at this point"); 0
2810 const char *BroadcastPrimitive = ----
2811 StringSwitch(BroadcastString) 0
2812 .Case("1to2", "{1to2}") 0
2813 .Case("1to4", "{1to4}") 0
2814 .Case("1to8", "{1to8}") 0
2815 .Case("1to16", "{1to16}") 0
2816 .Case("1to32", "{1to32}") 0
2817 .Default(nullptr); 0
2818 if (!BroadcastPrimitive) 0
2819 return TokError("Invalid memory broadcast primitive."); 0
2820 Parser.Lex(); // Eat trailing token of 1toN 0
2821 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::RCurly)) 0
2822 return TokError("Expected } at this point"); 0
2823 Parser.Lex(); // Eat "}" 0
2824 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateToken(BroadcastPrimitive, 0
2825 consumedToken)); ----
2826 // No AVX512 specific primitives can pass ----
2827 // after memory broadcasting, so return. ----
2828 return false; 0
2829 } else { 0
2830 // Parse either {k}{z}, {z}{k}, {k} or {z} ----
2831 // last one have no meaning, but GCC accepts it ----
2832 // Currently, we're just pass a '{' mark ----
2833 std::unique_ptr Z; 0
2834 if (ParseZ(Z, consumedToken)) 0
2835 return true; 0
2836 // Reaching here means that parsing of the allegadly '{z}' mark yielded ----
2837 // no errors. ----
2838 // Query for the need of further parsing for a {%k} mark ----
2839 if (!Z || getLexer().is(AsmToken::LCurly)) { 0
2840 SMLoc StartLoc = Z ? consumeToken() : consumedToken; 0
2841 // Parse an op-mask register mark ({%k}), which is now to be ----
2842 // expected ----
2843 MCRegister RegNo; 0
2844 SMLoc RegLoc; 0
2845 if (!parseRegister(RegNo, RegLoc, StartLoc) && 0
2846 X86MCRegisterClasses[X86::VK1RegClassID].contains(RegNo)) { 0
2847 if (RegNo == X86::K0) 0
2848 return Error(RegLoc, "Register k0 can't be used as write mask"); 0
2849 if (!getLexer().is(AsmToken::RCurly)) 0
2850 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(), "Expected } at this point"); 0
2851 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateToken("{", StartLoc)); 0
2852 Operands.push_back( 0
2853 X86Operand::CreateReg(RegNo, StartLoc, StartLoc)); 0
2854 Operands.push_back(X86Operand::CreateToken("}", consumeToken())); 0
2855 } else ----
2856 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(), 0
2857 "Expected an op-mask register at this point"); 0
2858 // {%k} mark is found, inquire for {z} ----
2859 if (getLexer().is(AsmToken::LCurly) && !Z) { 0
2860 // Have we've found a parsing error, or found no (expected) {z} mark ----
2861 // - report an error ----
2862 if (ParseZ(Z, consumeToken()) || !Z) 0
2863 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(), 0
2864 "Expected a {z} mark at this point"); 0
2865 ----
2866 } ----
2867 // '{z}' on its own is meaningless, hence should be ignored. ----
2868 // on the contrary - have it been accompanied by a K register, ----
2869 // allow it. ----
2870 if (Z) 0
2871 Operands.push_back(std::move(Z)); 0
2872 } ----
2873 } 0
2874 } ----
2875 return false; 0
2876 } ----
2877 ----
2878 /// ParseMemOperand: 'seg : disp(basereg, indexreg, scale)'. The '%ds:' prefix ----
